The paper presents a machine learning approach for forecasting electricity load profiles, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) for this task, which is a popular deep learning architecture used for image and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with time series forecasting, which could also fall under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
